3175,IssuesEvent,2015-05-01 04:18:00+00:00,5806020,rueckstiess/mtools,243499,victorhooi,,,opened,"mlaunch --help should mention it accepts arbitrary mongod/mongos flags, including -f/--config",[],[],0,"The mlaunch program will accept any valid `mongod`/`mongos` flags - this is an awesome feature.

It will also accept passing through a config file (using `-f` or `--config`), using a config file in the current directory.

This is mentioned in the mtools wiki on Github, however, it would be nice if this was also included in the `--help` output, or usage information (i.e. running just `mlaunch`) as well.",{},{}
3176,IssuesEvent,2018-04-29 23:53:26+00:00,5806020,rueckstiess/mtools,15554,stennie,,,closed,Add py36 environment for tox & Travis,"[{'id': 55790704, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/rueckstiess/mtools/labels/task', 'name': 'task', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}, {'id': 55790741, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/rueckstiess/mtools/labels/tests', 'name': 'tests', 'color': 'AAAAAA', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'stennie', 'id': 15554, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/15554?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stennie', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/stennie', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stennie/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stennie/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stennie/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stennie/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stennie/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stennie/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stennie/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stennie/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stennie/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"### Steps to set up py27 and py36 envs using `pyenv` on macOS

Install `pyenv`:
 - `brew install pyenv`

Build Python versions with `--enable-framework` for `matplotlib`:
 - `PYTHON_CONFIGURE_OPTS=""--enable-framework"" pyenv install 2.7.14`
 - `PYTHON_CONFIGURE_OPTS=""--enable-framework"" pyenv install 3.6.5`

Make sure `pyenv` versions are globally available as `python-2.7` and `python-3.6`:
 - `pyenv global 2.7.14 3.6.5`
",{},{}
