3193,IssuesEvent,2018-02-07 10:49:22+00:00,6794278,scanny/python-pptx,57103,jbq,,,opened,Adding a relation between shapes,[],[],0,"Hi, thanks for the great python-pptx library, good work!

I'm wondering how to add a relation between shapes.

I'm doing a basic `slide.shapes.add_chart()` and it works nice, and I needed to add a caption in this chart, so I added a `slide.shapes.add_textbox()` and it works nice too.  But I'd like the text box to be included in the chart, ie add a relation from chart to textbox.  This is achieved with rel files AFAICT but can't find an API for that.  I also couldn't find a group feature, apart from the refused PR.

It seems odd that a chart caption is left unrelated to the chart itself.  Customer need to be able to copy/paste the chart and move it around as a whole.

Any idea?",{},{}
