3223,IssuesEvent,2015-10-14 19:45:11+00:00,28882767,tkem/mopidy-mobile,2833077,tkem,,,opened,Added playlist not shown in playlists in current v1.4 beta,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/tkem/mopidy-mobile/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],0,"In v1.4 beta,

- Go to tab ""Playlists""
- Select edit mode.
- Add new playlist
- Save

The new playlist will not be shown in edit mode, nor will it be shown when going back to playlists overview. One has to manually pull-to-refresh for the new playlist to be shown.

Reason seems to be that scopes ""stacked"" in a tab's history do not receive angular broadcast events in Ionic. This may affect routing in general, and must be investigated further. Possible solution would be to make ""playlist.add"" a descendant of ""playlists"", but app routing has to be reviewed for similar cases.
",{},{}
3231,IssuesEvent,2017-04-10 11:46:04+00:00,8292338,ultrabug/py3status,56311,tobes,,,closed,MPRIS: won't catch the player if the module is launched before any player,[],[],7,"Hi,

There is an annoying bug in the MPRIS module:

