3502,IssuesEvent,2016-12-06 08:58:07+00:00,69090889,hardbyte/python-can,855189,hardbyte,,,closed,canplayer - stream captured frames to virtual device,"[{'id': 448741913, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/hardbyte/python-can/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 448749841, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/hardbyte/python-can/labels/proposal', 'name': 'proposal', 'color': 'ededed', 'default': False}]",[],0,"While capturing a db file is useful for offline analysis it can be very useful to ""replay"" a captured session.

This issue is to create such a command line tool that works with our supported formats - at least the `.db`.

Possible flags (from `canplayer`):
```
Usage can_player.py <options> input-file
-c CAN channel
-i python-can interface
-t ignore timestamps (send immediately at minimum gap)
-g <ms> minimum gap between sent frames
-s <s> skip gaps greater than 's' seconds
-v print sent CAN frames
