3511,IssuesEvent,2017-01-07 00:44:53+00:00,9760336,iheanyi/bandcamp-dl,1984403,Evolution0,,,closed,File integrity check redux,"[{'id': 37848718, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/iheanyi/bandcamp-dl/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'Evolution0', 'id': 1984403, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1984403?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Evolution0', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/Evolution0', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Evolution0/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Evolution0/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Evolution0/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Evolution0/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Evolution0/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Evolution0/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Evolution0/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Evolution0/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Evolution0/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",2,"The first time around it was implemented too primitively and that is my fault for assuming too much 😸 

This time I've broken it down into a more robust process:
1. Get content-length header
2. Get local file size in bytes
3. Calculate size in bytes of the metadata added to each track
4. Subtract metadata size in bytes from the local file size
5. Add metadata size in bytes to the content-length
6. Compare the final sizes

Another thing is that we encode files regardless of if they are complete or not, a simple check with mutagen of the track duration against the track duration listed in the metadata before encoding should fix that. (possibly initiating a retry or skip track + error message?",{},{}
