3568,IssuesEvent,2018-03-28 21:09:39+00:00,79157422,klahnakoski/mo-logs,2334429,klahnakoski,,,opened,Detect recursive loops,[],[],0,"The mo-logs lib has a problem reporting errors when the problem is a recursive loop

```python
def oh_no():
    try:
        oh_no()
    except Exception as e:
        Log.error(""this is a problem"", e)
```

The `oh_no()` will overload the stack; Python will raise a legitimate exception; as the loop unrolls, the chain of causes gets very long; serializing the chain will result in a stack overflow because it is as long as the overflow!

If we can detect call loops we can emit a special ""recursive loop"" exception that will consume recursive stack traces, making for a shorter error report, and add the ability to detail the loop that caused the problem. ",{},{}
