6024,IssuesEvent,2017-01-25 04:08:22+00:00,38095954,eternnoir/pyTelegramBotAPI,15062597,bryzgaloff,,,opened,Exception handling best practice,[],[],0,"pyTelegramBotAPI version: 2.3.0
OS: Windows 10 / Ubuntu 16.04.1
Python version: 3.5.1

Is there any way to handle exceptions during task execution? As I can see, pyTelegramBotAPI does it itself [here](https://github.com/eternnoir/pyTelegramBotAPI/blob/master/telebot/util.py#L59):
```python
except:
    logger.debug(""Exception occurred"")
    self.exc_info = sys.exc_info()
    self.exception_event.set()

    if self.exception_callback:
        self.exception_callback(self, self.exc_info)
    self.continue_event.wait()
```
So I had to change this code to the one you can see below to be able to handle exceptions in the custom way (default telebot logging was not informative at all):
```python
except Exception as e:
    logger.error(type(e).__name__ + "" occurred, args="" + str(e.args) + ""\n"" + traceback.format_exc())
    self.exc_info = sys.exc_info()
    self.exception_event.set()

    if self.exception_callback:
        self.exception_callback(self, self.exc_info)
    self.continue_event.wait()
```
I also have to do some more actions while handling different exceptions so I'm wondering whether there is a better way to handle exceptions. Of course it's not really convenient to change the library code on every platform. Please point me to the right direction. Thank you in advance.",{},{}
