8022,IssuesEvent,2018-02-06 13:23:15+00:00,648332,assimp/assimp,6006874,mabuchner,265533,assimp,opened,FileSystemFilter should be integrated into DefaultIOSystem,[],[],0,"I'm trying to convince Assimp to use my custom filesystem library. Thereby I noticed, that each call to [`BaseImporter::ReadFile`](https://github.com/assimp/assimp/blob/v4.1.0/code/BaseImporter.cpp#L80) will [wrap](https://github.com/assimp/assimp/blob/v4.1.0/code/BaseImporter.cpp#L89) any `IOSystem` inside a `FileSystemFilter` (see also #1773).

I'm not really sure what the purpose of the `FileSystemFilter` class is, but it seems like it's doing some assumption on how the filesystem behaves. Since a user might provide a custom `IOSystem` this assumptions might not be correct. The `FileSystemFilter` might even turn a valid path into something, that is not valid anymore.

Therefore the functionality of the `FileSystemFilter` class should be integrated into the `DefaultIOSystem`, for which those assumptions seem to be correct.",{},{}
