8165,IssuesEvent,2018-04-26 20:03:47+00:00,24774658,boto/boto3,2643092,JordonPhillips,327752,boto,closed,Bucket creation fails when region is us-east-1,[],[],1,"If you don't set a default region, boto3 assumes `us-east-1`. Then if you try to create a bucket and pass `eu-west-1` as your `LocationConstraint`, the bucket creation fails with a `InvalidLocationConstraint` error. This offers a poor user experience as the only way to fix this is a bunch of if to make sure you only pass the LocationConstraint when you have to.",{},{}
8173,IssuesEvent,2017-07-19 21:04:43+00:00,6670942,boto/botocore,1935727,joguSD,327752,boto,closed,Minor issue in retryhandler - random.random() can return 0,"[{'id': 19177682, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/boto/botocore/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': True}]",[],3,"in the function delay_exponential, at [line 53](https://github.com/boto/botocore/blob/c632931a6cc5eab4113c976d430bcb9c059f829f/botocore/retryhandler.py#L53), base is set to random.random(). However, the documentation (and the other branch of that if) declare that ""Base must be greater than 0."", and the [spec for random.random()](https://docs.python.org/3/library/random.html#random.random) is that it will return a float in the range [0.0, 1.0), which includes 0.0. 

Thus, in extremely rare cases, time_to_sleep could repeatedly be 0, defeating the purpose of exponential backoff.",{},{}
8181,IssuesEvent,2017-07-20 17:25:16+00:00,6670942,boto/botocore,703870,timuralp,327752,boto,closed,"Setting Content-Length still results in Transfer-Encoding set to ""chunked""","[{'id': 217064623, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/boto/botocore/labels/closing-soon-if-no-response', 'name': 'closing-soon-if-no-response', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}, {'id': 19177683, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/boto/botocore/labels/wontfix', 'name': 'wontfix', 'color': 'ffffff', 'default': True}]",[],8,"I'm encountering an issue where uploading a file and setting the ContentLength header in the `put_object()` call still result in the Transfer-Encoding being set to chunked. This, in turn, results in the failure to upload a file, with the following error:

```
2016-05-05 23:37:25,374 botocore.vendored.requests.packages.urllib3.connectionpool [DEBUG] ""PUT /AUTH_test/test/bash_logout HTTP/1.1"" 501 None
DEBUG:botocore.vendored.requests.packages.urllib3.connectionpool:""PUT /AUTH_test/test/bash_logout HTTP/1.1"" 501 None
2016-05-05 23:37:25,388 botocore.parsers [DEBUG] Response headers: {'x-amz-id-2': 'ZTpbRioCBOJR3RwdOUDSHgwMBABo8O8oFSpmvyG7F3turQ6Q9MPRg5JMjxI49Rk57MXudMm6lSQ=', 'server': 'AmazonS3', 'transfer-encoding': 'chunked', 'connection': 'close', 'x-amz-request-id': '008D7F33A19459E1', 'date': 'Thu, 05 May 2016 23:37:17 GMT', 'content-type': 'application/xml'}
DEBUG:botocore.parsers:Response headers: {'x-amz-id-2': 'ZTpbRioCBOJR3RwdOUDSHgwMBABo8O8oFSpmvyG7F3turQ6Q9MPRg5JMjxI49Rk57MXudMm6lSQ=', 'server': 'AmazonS3', 'transfer-encoding': 'chunked', 'connection': 'close', 'x-amz-request-id': '008D7F33A19459E1', 'date': 'Thu, 05 May 2016 23:37:17 GMT', 'content-type': 'application/xml'}
2016-05-05 23:37:25,397 botocore.parsers [DEBUG] Response body:
<?xml version=""1.0"" encoding=""UTF-8""?>
<Error><Code>NotImplemented</Code><Message>A header you provided implies functionality that is not implemented</Message><Header>Transfer-Encoding</Header><RequestId>008D7F33A19459E1</RequestId><HostId>ZTpbRioCBOJR3RwdOUDSHgwMBABo8O8oFSpmvyG7F3turQ6Q9MPRg5JMjxI49Rk57MXudMm6lSQ=</HostId></Error>
```

I believe the issue is in the `botocore/vendored/requests/models.py` file, specifically:

```
440         if is_stream:
441             body = data
442 
443             if files:
444                 raise NotImplementedError('Streamed bodies and files are mutually exclusive.')
445 
446             if length is not None:
447                 self.headers['Content-Length'] = builtin_str(length)
448             else:
449                 self.headers['Transfer-Encoding'] = 'chunked'
```

My invocation is as follows:

```
s3_client.put_object(Bucket=self.aws_bucket, Key=key,
                     Body=input_stream,
                     ContentLength=length)
```

and I expect it to set the Content-Length and not use the chunked encoding. I'll submit a patch to consider the contents of the headers when determining which encoding to use (which also unblocks my usage of boto3).
",{},{}
8184,IssuesEvent,2016-03-08 01:17:43+00:00,6670942,boto/botocore,9458045,migtor,327752,boto,opened,Applying sigv4 to requests to URLs wtih a path containing '.' or '..' can fail,[],[],0,"This happens if `.` or `..` are at the beginning of a path segment: they get stripped out, but that's correct only if the whole path segment is `.` or `..`.

For example, generating a signature for a request to `https://service.amazonaws.com/path/.somepath/` would be rejected by the services, because when the path is normalised, it gets converted to `/path/somepath/`.

See pull request: #827 ",{},{}
8191,IssuesEvent,2018-04-23 01:27:52+00:00,6670942,boto/botocore,7205587,ps-jay,327752,boto,opened,Upstream documentation issue: AutoScalingGroupNamesType as used in DescribeAutoScalingGroups API call,[],[],0,"I understand that `service-2.json` files are auto-generated, so I haven't opened a PR here.

The issue is that a `DescribeAutoScalingGroups` call with more than 50 group names provided in the `AutoScalingGroupNames` list results in an exception:

```botocore.exceptions.ClientError: An error occurred (ValidationError) when calling the DescribeAutoScalingGroups operation: The number of group names that may be passed in is limited to 50```

Ideally, this should be documented as a restriction.",{},{}
