8883,IssuesEvent,2018-01-02 18:38:01+00:00,37571213,minio/minio-py,21183913,mlinsky,695951,minio,opened,[SSL: CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED] ,[],[],0,"Hi, i am trying to upload a png file into my minio server that requires ssl, i am following along with what code you have on this page https://docs.minio.io/docs/how-to-use-aws-sdk-for-python-with-minio-server . I have also tried to write code that uses python requests but i keep getting the same error. I have tried my combination of adding certs, auth, and params that included the access key an secret key of minio along with the cert file for the specific project im working on. this is what i currently have in my code. url is the url of the minio server ""home"" page not the login. here is the path to the image and name is the name of the image.

```
s3 = boto3.resource('s3',
                                    endpoint_url=url,
                                    aws_access_key_id=key_id,
                                    aws_secret_access_key=access_key,
                                    config=Config(signature_version='s3v4'),
                                    region_name='us-east-1')
                s3.Bucket('screenshots').upload_file(here+'/'+name+'.png', name+'.png')

                print('Uploaded ' + name + '.png to the screenshots bucket.')
```",{},{}
8889,IssuesEvent,2018-02-26 23:42:11+00:00,37571213,minio/minio-py,1700901,deekoder,695951,minio,closed,Support copy_object for all sizes,"[{'id': 844579277, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/minio/minio-py/labels/help-wanted', 'name': 'help-wanted', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}, {'id': 578346399, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/minio/minio-py/labels/priority:%20medium', 'name': 'priority: medium', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}]",[],2,Requirements are detailed here - https://github.com/minio/minio-go/issues/617,{},{}
8891,IssuesEvent,2017-05-04 20:15:28+00:00,37571213,minio/minio-py,18228330,fazpu,695951,minio,opened,Make possible to return partial URL,[],[],0,"Hi,

Problem:
* minio is deployed in docker swarm cluster under service name **minio_service**
* When connecting to minio service via the minio.Minio client, I would input the endpoint parameter as **minio_service**
* Now, when I call e.g. the presigned_get_object method, the reutrned url is e.g. **http://minio_service/example_bucket/example_file...**

Of course, such URL does not exist and the request would fail.

Required state:
* there should be option to return only the partial address, e.g. example_bucket/example_file...
* I propose minio.Minio method should have additional argument **partial_url** with default value False. If set to True, only partial URLs would be returned.

Why I am interested:
* I am currently working on large PR for django-minio-storage (https://github.com/tomhoule/django-minio-storage/pull/14)
* It is necessary to combine django-defined base static/media URL with the file path in minio",{},{}
8906,IssuesEvent,2016-07-13 07:35:31+00:00,27086567,scrapinghub/dateparser,1888537,waqasshabbir,699596,scrapinghub,closed,Can't parse Chinese date `2016年06月30日09时30分`,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/scrapinghub/dateparser/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],0,"It can parse `2016年06月30日` but `2016年06月30日09时30分` or `2016年06月30日 09时30分`

 `2016年06月30日09时30分` means 2016-06-30 09:30",{},{}
8909,IssuesEvent,2015-02-09 22:10:29+00:00,27086567,scrapinghub/dateparser,2597566,Allactaga,699596,scrapinghub,closed,Configuration,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/scrapinghub/dateparser/labels/easy', 'name': 'easy', 'color': '009800'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/scrapinghub/dateparser/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],0,"It looks that we need to parametrize parsing behavior. Instead of keep adding parameters to the parse function I suggest to create a Registry changeable with `configure(key=value)` function. 
Example settings could be `NO_DATES_FROM_FUTURE` (to parse dates from web, where some times pieces from the created date is missing and we are assuming past) or `SUPPORT_BEFORE_COMMON_ERA` (to use custom datetime class inherited from datetime but supporting Astronomical year numbering)",{},{}
