9056,IssuesEvent,2017-08-02 14:20:31+00:00,60500064,Simplistix/errorhandler,1117703,dhimmel,809412,Simplistix,closed,errorhandler disables default logging output to stderr,[],[],4,"Great package! It does exactly what I needed. This repo took me a while to find, but it's an honor to be the first user to star it! The use case it solves seems like it should be pretty common, especially with the growing use of continuous integration builds. I [answered a StackOverflow question](https://stackoverflow.com/a/45446664/4651668) with this package.

I'm adding `errorhandler` to our project in https://github.com/greenelab/manubot/pull/2. One thing that confused me at first was that adding error handler suppressed the default logging to stderr. I'm not sure whether this is intentional or a bug. Anyways, here's the [code I used](https://github.com/dhimmel/manubot/blob/a55158c57d7ac15344bbe622b9684a34dad0a6cc/manubot/manubot.py#L258-L263) to get the stderr logging back:

``` python
error_handler = errorhandler.ErrorHandler()
logger = logging.getLogger()
logger.setLevel(getattr(logging, args.log_level))
stream_handler = logging.StreamHandler(stream=sys.stderr)
logger.addHandler(stream_handler)
```

Is this the simplest workaround?",{},{}
9061,IssuesEvent,2018-05-27 00:54:52+00:00,27921304,Polyconseil/zbarlight,24973,AndreMiras,818669,Polyconseil,opened,Detecting multiple code types,[],[],0,"I'm currently migrating my app (https://github.com/AndreMiras/QrScan) and libraries (https://github.com/kivy-garden/garden.zbarcam) from zbar (built-in module) to zbarlight, and I came across this: https://github.com/Polyconseil/zbarlight/blob/2.0/src/zbarlight/_zbarlight.c#L27
```c
zbar_image_scanner_set_config(scanner, 0, ZBAR_CFG_ENABLE, 0); /* disable all symbologies */
zbar_image_scanner_set_config(scanner, symbologie, ZBAR_CFG_ENABLE, 1);
```
I can imagine enabling only one type at a time is currently a feature of this project. But I think it would be great to have the choice to enable multiple features at a time with a list, e.g.
```python
zbarlight.scan_codes(['qrcode', 'ean13'], pil_image)
```",{},{}
