9360,IssuesEvent,2015-03-10 11:59:03+00:00,8481938,mozilla-services/konfig,546692,leplatrem,1066228,mozilla-services,opened,Handling defaults and environment variables,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla-services/konfig/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c'}]",[],0,"In my Pyramid application, I want to gather all options and values in one place.

I would like the config values to be resolved this way:

1. env using upercase
1. local app config
1. app default values

Using konfig, it looks like I could assemble extends and overrides to accomplish this...

```ini
#app/config/defaults.ini
[auth]
user = alice
key = abcd
```

```ini
#app/config/env.ini
[auth]
user = ${AUTH_USER}
key = ${AUTH_KEY}
```

```ini
#production.ini
[DEFAULT]
overrides = app/config/env.ini
extends = app/config/default.ini

[auth]
key = xyz
```

Pros
* No specific code in my application, I always assume the value is defined in the final config
* Very modular

Cons
* Application config should refer to env and default paths (absolute or relative)


Does it looks like a good idea to use konfig for that ?

",{},{}
