received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",8,"In relation to [#195](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-accounts/issues/195) in invenio-accounts, after creating the database with:
`flask alembic upgrade heads`

dropping the tables: `flask db drop` leaves these two in the db:
```
+----------+-----------------+--------+----------+
| Schema   | Name            | Type   | Owner    |
|----------+-----------------+--------+----------|
| public   | alembic_version | table  | postgres |
| public   | transaction     | table  | postgres |
+----------+-----------------+--------+----------+
```

For the transaction table, alembic downgrade would delete it fine but it is not currently found in this [loop](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-db/blob/master/invenio_db/cli.py#L83) <- this is wrong, it is registered but can't be dropped because of the transaction_id_seq depending on it.",{},{}
