9745,IssuesEvent,2016-02-03 18:53:34+00:00,5070149,kivy/buildozer,788023,akshayaurora,1266152,kivy,closed,"pip no longer has a --download-cache option, so downloading requirements has stopped working",[],[],2,"This is the error:-
```

# Command failed: pip install
--download-cache=/home/ngoonee/.buildozer/cache
--target=/home/data/Coding/buildozer/.buildozer/applibs Whoosh
#
# Buildozer failed to execute the last command
# The error might be hidden in the log above this error
# Please read the full log, and search for it before
# raising an issue with buildozer itself.
# In case of a bug report, please add a full log with log_level = 2
```

I have pip 8.0.2, which doesn't have the download-cache option.

Fix is to remove the download-cache option in `__init__.py`

```
        #self.cmd('pip install --download-cache={} --target={} {}'.format(
        self.cmd('pip install --target={} {}'.format(
                #self.global_cache_dir, self.applibs_dir, module),
                self.applibs_dir, module
```

