10202,IssuesEvent,2015-04-14 20:50:24+00:00,12629378,gems-uff/noworkflow,327789,JoaoFelipe,1486707,gems-uff,closed,IPython Required?,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/gems-uff/noworkflow/labels/0.9.3', 'name': '0.9.3', 'color': 'bfe5bf'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/gems-uff/noworkflow/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],1,"I think that the `.now.ipython` import in `noworkflow/__init__.py` means that IPython is required to run noWorkflow conflicting the README. However, I tried moving that import inside the `load_ipython_extension` method, and that did allow the help message to be printed without IPython installed.",{},{}
10212,IssuesEvent,2015-07-29 20:08:53+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,8152173,hellsing71,1505683,FortAwesome,opened,Icon Request: fa-ce-mark,[],[],0,"No, it's not a new face icon.

The CE marking is superwidely used, it is a mandatory conformity marking for products sold within the European Economic Area (EEA). It looks like this:

![280px-conformite_europeenne_ logo svg](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8152173/8968314/ac3fdc06-363c-11e5-853b-54119e436b34.png)

Important: its not a simple pair of uppercase C+E letters. This is how it must be drawn:

![draw-ce-marking](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8152173/8968406/3aecafec-363d-11e5-8c23-327f83a90de4.png)

It could be used on manufacturers' and e-commerce sites that delivers to or within the European Union.

Maybe our friends over the ocean are interested in an FCC compliance mark, too.",{},{}
