10551,IssuesEvent,2016-09-30 18:15:56+00:00,12345160,ansible/tower-cli,1385596,AlanCoding,1507452,ansible,opened,Support uploading JT survey,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ansible/tower-cli/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ansible/tower-cli/labels/needs_devel', 'name': 'needs_devel', 'color': 'e6e6e6'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ansible/tower-cli/labels/P3', 'name': 'P3', 'color': '009800'}]",[],0,"Although tower-cli supports creating different types of job templates, you can't add a survey. This should be easy to implement as a generic variables field. In addition to this, there is a different endpoint the user needs to hit in order to GET the survey spec. Proposal:

 - add `--survey-spec` parameter to job templates
 - add `--survey-enabled` boolean parameter, document in survey-spec help text that this needs to be set
 - add a `tower-cli job_template get_survey` command to print the survey spec contents

This would be a little clunky to use, but it would get the job done.",{},{}
