10979,IssuesEvent,2017-05-24 18:02:17+00:00,81612762,trailofbits/manticore,2467355,mossberg,2314423,trailofbits,opened,Control whether libraries are loaded or not,"[{'id': 579677741, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/trailofbits/manticore/labels/loader', 'name': 'loader', 'color': '1d76db', 'default': False}, {'id': 579676078, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/trailofbits/manticore/labels/performance', 'name': 'performance', 'color': 'bfdadc', 'default': False}]",[],0,"When analyzing a dynamic binary in Manticore, Manticore always loads the libraries specified in the binary. It might possibly be desirable to disable this functionality, if those libraries are not necessary for the intended analysis, or if the libraries are unavailable, as this would improve the performance of Manticore's initialization.",{},{}
10983,IssuesEvent,2017-12-23 00:11:26+00:00,81612762,trailofbits/manticore,2467355,mossberg,2314423,trailofbits,closed,readthedocs build fails,"[{'id': 579674255, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/trailofbits/manticore/labels/documentation', 'name': 'documentation', 'color': 'd93f0b', 'default': False}, {'id': 589015854, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/trailofbits/manticore/labels/easy', 'name': 'easy', 'color': 'bfdadc', 'default': False}]",[],0,"This happens because it tries to build z3 from source and is oom killed

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2467355/33100161-5e586464-cee1-11e7-95f8-30ab092ae0ec.png)

They do `setup.py install --force` to install the package, which doesn't use wheels like pip does. This is why it is installing z3 from source.

We might be able to hack around this by using their REATHEDOCS environment variable in our setup.py script to remove the z3 dependency only when rtd is trying to install

https://docs.readthedocs.io/en/latest/faq.html#how-do-i-change-behavior-for-read-the-docs",{},{}
