11001,IssuesEvent,2018-05-07 20:31:04+00:00,30509483,clab/dynet,5944369,AbhilashaRavichander,2374376,clab,opened,Initializing Lookup Matrix for Tensors,[],[],0,"Hi,

When I tried initializing a 4-d tensor with an appropriately shaped numpy array using init_from_array, I get ""TypeError: 'only size-1 arrays can be converted to Python scalars""

This was the code snippet that created the bug:
```
def loadEmbedding_rand(path, word_indices):
    n = len(word_indices)
    m = 300  # Word Embedding dimensions
    emb = np.empty((n, m), dtype=np.float32)
    emb[:, :] = np.random.normal(size=(n, m))
    # Explicitly assign embedding of <PAD> to be zeros.
    emb[0:2, :] = np.zeros((1, m), dtype=""float32"")
    with open(path, 'r') as f:
        for i, line in enumerate(f):
            s = line.split()
            if s[0] in word_indices:
                try:
                    emb[word_indices[s[0]], :] = np.asarray(s[1:])
                except Exception as e:
                    print(e)
                    continue
    return np.reshape(emb, (n,1,1,m))

wembed = model.add_lookup_parameters((len(word_indices), 1, 1, EMB_SIZE))
wembed.init_from_array(word_embeds)
```

Initialization using 
`wembed = model.add_lookup_parameters((len(word_indices), 1, 1, EMB_SIZE), init = dy.NumpyInitializer(word_embeds))`, works however.",{},{}
11002,IssuesEvent,2017-09-27 02:48:10+00:00,30509483,clab/dynet,398875,neubig,2374376,clab,opened,DyNet no longer searches for open GPU,"[{'id': 439661365, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/clab/dynet/labels/moderate%20bug', 'name': 'moderate bug', 'color': 'e99695', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'xunzhang', 'id': 554159, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/554159?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xunzhang', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/xunzhang', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xunzhang/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xunzhang/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xunzhang/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xunzhang/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xunzhang/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xunzhang/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xunzhang/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xunzhang/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/xunzhang/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"DyNet used to search for an open GPU and pick the one with the most open memory. This was convenient behavior, but now apparently when setting the `--dynet-gpu` flag in Python it simply allocates to GPU0. It would be nice if we could get the old behavior back.",{},{}
