11038,IssuesEvent,2016-11-01 14:28:19+00:00,30509483,clab/dynet,263363,danielhers,2374376,clab,opened,Inconsistent invalid argument exceptions,[],[],0,"I'm using the Python bindings and I [use](https://github.com/danielhers/ucca/blob/dynet/parsing/classifiers/nn/feedforward.py#L45) `reshape` to change a batch of embeddings into one long vector.
The same code sometimes works fine and sometimes fails with the [error](https://travis-ci.org/danielhers/ucca/jobs/172277222) `Bad arguments to Reshape: {3200}, {10X32}`.
In the same network I [use](https://github.com/danielhers/ucca/blob/dynet/parsing/classifiers/nn/feedforward.py#L59) matrix multiplication, and this also sometimes fails the [error](https://travis-ci.org/danielhers/ucca/jobs/172277231) `Mismatched input dimensions in MatrixMultiply: [{200} {200}]`.
This happens both on my computer and on Travis CI.
I think what is common to these failures is that the model I'm running is either loaded from a file, or is not the first model I'm building in the same run. The errors do not always occur when this is the case, though.
Perhaps there is some cache I can clear when I'm done with a model?",{},{}
