11189,IssuesEvent,2016-08-17 19:51:53+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python,242750,tseaver,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,Expose V1 entity versions / conflict detection,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/labels/datastore', 'name': 'datastore', 'color': '0052cc'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],0,"From:

- https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/pull/2107/files#r75191382
- https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/pull/2107/files#r75192591
- https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/pull/2107/files#r75191517


See the docs for the new (seemingly related) features:

- [`EntityResult.version`](https://cloud.google.com/datastore/reference/rest/v1/EntityResult#FIELDS.version)  field
- [`Mutation.base_version`](https://cloud.google.com/datastore/reference/rest/v1/projects/commit#Mutation.FIELDS.base_version) field
- [`MutationResult.conflictDetected`](https://cloud.google.com/datastore/reference/rest/v1/projects/commit#MutationResult.FIELDS.conflict_detected) field",{},{}
11192,IssuesEvent,2016-07-11 19:30:25+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python,242750,tseaver,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,'gax-google-pubsub-v1' and 'gax-google-logging-v2' wreck the 'google.protobuf' namespace,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/labels/gRPC', 'name': 'gRPC', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/labels/logging', 'name': 'logging', 'color': 'bfdadc'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/labels/pubsub', 'name': 'pubsub', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],0,"/cc @bjwatson, @tbetbetbe, @rok987

The failure only shows up when things are installed via `easy_install` (vs. `pip`).  The two packages each include and empty `google/protobuf/__init__.py`, without any namespace package declaration for it (or any purpose).  When installed in a particular order via `easy_install` / `setup.py develop`, the bogus `google.protobuf` package ends up higher on `sys.path` than the real `google.protobuf`, and mayhem ensues.

The fix would be to just drop them from the sdists altogether.",{},{}
11199,IssuesEvent,2016-02-02 15:11:30+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python,3934878,asaidomar,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,ValueError when tring to pulish message (V 0.9),[],[],0,"When using the full path of the topic like this:

```
class PubSubClient(CloudClient):

    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        client = pubsub.Client(
            project=self.config.get(""project""), credentials=self.credentials)

        self.client = client.topic(""/projects/myprojectname/topics/files.dev"")

    def publish(self, message):
        self.client.publish(bytes(message, encoding=""utf8""))
```

I got the following error:

```
  File ""C:\Python34\lib\json\decoder.py"", line 343, in decode
    obj, end = self.raw_decode(s, idx=_w(s, 0).end())
  File ""C:\Python34\lib\json\decoder.py"", line 361, in raw_decode
    raise ValueError(errmsg(""Expecting value"", s, err.value)) from None
ValueError: Expecting value: line 1 column 1 (char 0)
```

It's seem that the html response is decoded rather than the JSON response. 
When using the trailing name of the topic ""files.dev"", the message is published.




",{},{}
