11278,IssuesEvent,2017-10-16 23:04:38+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python,520669,dhermes,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,Add `.devN` suffixes to all version numbers,"[{'id': 131855319, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python/labels/packaging', 'name': 'packaging', 'color': 'fad8c7', 'default': False}]",[],0,"I propose we add `.devN` suffixes to all version numbers. This way we can accurately reflect, e.g. that `google-cloud-pubsub` depends on `google-cloud-core >= 0.28.0.dev1` rather than a released version of `google-cloud-core`.

Ref: https://snarky.ca/how-i-manage-package-version-numbers/

----

From https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python/issues/4186#issuecomment-336531198",{},{}
11284,IssuesEvent,2017-07-20 14:35:38+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python,17654512,umutberkbilgic,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,[ Request ] ,[],[],0,"I love Google Cloud Datastore for Python, after  7-8 hours of fiddling around with it, it finally works as I want it to. However one quick thing that could make life easier is if there was a return flag from functions (such as client.delete(key)) as front end could save a lot of time (both during execution and while developing). It seems to return, well, nothing at the mean time unlike client.get(key) which has a return that can be used as a simple flag. Serverless architecture is awesome but latency can be a real issue (although Google is pretty good, it is still noticable). Every line of code matters (efficieny-wise) and overall I feel more returns would allow frontend developers more tools while decreasing overall server pokes. Sorry if this should not go here by the way.

Cheers.",{},{}
