11348,IssuesEvent,2017-05-11 02:02:34+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python,806423,matrixl,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,(google-cloud-vision) enum34 should not be installed on Python 3.4+,[],[],0,"The enum34 breaks my code (python3.6), it is a known issue that enum34 doesn't work on Python 3.4+

suggested fix in vision/setup.py

```python
REQUIREMENTS = [
-    'enum34',
    'google-cloud-core >= 0.24.0, < 0.25dev',
    'gapic-google-cloud-vision-v1 >= 0.90.3, < 0.91dev',
]

+if sys.version_info < (3, 4):
+    # Backport of Python 3.4 enums to earlier versions
+   REQUIREMENTS.append('enum34')

setup(
    name='google-cloud-vision',
    version='0.24.0',
    description='Python Client for Google Cloud Vision',
    long_description=README,
    namespace_packages=[
        'google',
        'google.cloud',
    ],
    packages=find_packages(exclude=('tests*',)),
    install_requires=REQUIREMENTS,
    **SETUP_BASE
)
```
",{},{}
11353,IssuesEvent,2018-05-14 18:03:13+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python,167797,michaelsafyan,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,"Please restore ""google.cloud.monitoring.Client'",[],[],0,"I understand that this code was hand-generated. Rather than deleting this code, though, it would be ideal if its creation were simply automated. Breaking existing code that references this library is not ideal.

Code that previously used:
`from google.cloud import monitoring

client = monitoring.Client()
# ...
`

... shouldn't be broken when upgrading to newer versions. Ideally, the definition of ""monitoring.Client"" should simply be auto-generated so that it is not additional, manually-maintained code. But it should still be there as an interface to simplify the usage of the API.",{},{}
