11741,IssuesEvent,2018-06-20 15:43:31+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Shared futures regularly allocate 3kb,"[{'id': 268094252, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwyNjgwOTQyNTI=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/engine', 'name': 'engine', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}]",[],0,"From profiling memory usage on OSX (using Instruments, which has become useful since we switched to the system allocator via `cdylib`), it appears that `Shared` futures very regularly (perhaps all of them) result in a 3kb memory allocation for one of their internal HashMaps. This appears to account for about 1/3 of our allocations.

