12610,IssuesEvent,2016-05-01 12:46:08+00:00,2113510,crossbario/autobahn-python,233340,oberstet,5656948,crossbario,opened,Deprecate wsaccel and replace with Ueberschall,[],[],0,"Autobahn can make use of `wsaccel` to accelerate WebSocket:

* accelerated functions are UTF8 validation and XOR masking
* wsaccel is based on Cython

`wsaccel` has a couple of downsides:

* it doesn't make Autobahn faster on PyPy (since it is using Cython, which doesn't blend well with PyPy)
* it's acceleration is limited
* there are [no Windows wheels](https://github.com/methane/wsaccel/issues/12)

Some years ago I wrote code that provides acceleration using SIMD vector intrinsics for such stuff that is **way** faster. This is superscalar code making use of modern CPUs and blows away wsaccel, PyPy (pure Python) and C++. This code interfaces to Python via CFFI, and hence runs fast there too.

Here: https://github.com/crossbario/ueberschall

Autobahn should use Uberschall if available and deprecate wsaccel.",{},{}
12612,IssuesEvent,2017-03-18 22:25:03+00:00,2113510,crossbario/autobahn-python,233340,oberstet,5656948,crossbario,closed,Insecure masking key selection?,"[{'id': 172662, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/crossbario/autobahn-python/labels/websocket', 'name': 'websocket', 'color': '0b02e1', 'default': False}]",[],22,"RFC 6455 says:

> The masking key is a 32-bit value chosen at random by the client.
> When preparing a masked frame, the client MUST pick a fresh masking
> key from the set of allowed 32-bit values. The masking key needs to
> be unpredictable; thus, the masking key MUST be derived from a strong
> source of entropy, and the masking key for a given frame MUST NOT
> make it simple for a server/proxy to predict the masking key for a
> subsequent frame. The unpredictability of the masking key is
> essential to prevent authors of malicious applications from selecting
> the bytes that appear on the wire.

But if I'm reading the code right, autobahn appears to [select masks using random.getrandbits](https://github.com/crossbario/autobahn-python/blob/57c2f87d7750fa76165a06f2140b7f33f2f093d0/autobahn/websocket/protocol.py#L1800), which uses Python's default Mersenne Twister-based RNG. The Mersenne Twister is inappropriate for security-sensitive applications because its future outputs can be predicted by observing previous outputs. (I.e., seeing the first N masks lets you predict the future masks.)",{},{}
12619,IssuesEvent,2016-02-09 18:46:48+00:00,2113510,crossbario/autobahn-python,61136,pramukta,5656948,crossbario,opened,Unicode chars break the library when WAMP Debug is used with JSON Serialization,[],[],0,"So I found this kindof subtle issue.  Specifically, when `self.logFrames = True`, the `logTxFrames` and `logRxFrames` methods in `autobahn/websocket/protocol.py` call `binascii.b2a_hex` on the frame payload.  This is fine when the payload is msgpack binary since that has been encoded into a byte array already.  However, when the payload is JSON it is a unicode payload which gets implicitly converted to a byte array using the ascii codec.  As a result, if there is a unicode character in there (for example `u""\u2639""`) an exception is thrown from the logger that looks like this:

```Shell
