exceptions.UnicodeDecodeError: 'ascii' codec can't decode byte 0xe2 in position 11: ordinal not in range(128)
```

I replicated this in an isolated case by modifying the `rpc/arguments` example, enabling debugging and adding in that unicode character to the payload.  I used the bonefish router to test because it was easy to disable msgpack on the command line (and I had a build handy) but this exception is post-invocation and pre-response exception so it would happen in any router.  Disabling debug mode makes things work again.

Any thoughts on how to best address it?  Thanks.",{},{}
