12916,IssuesEvent,2017-02-03 22:09:19+00:00,53438969,globus/globus-cli,6742946,tuecke,6120321,globus,opened,config filename,[],[],0,"Somewhere in the config commands there should be an easy way to get back the config filename.  Its printed as part of the output message on various commands, but I couldn't find a command to just get back the name.  Options:

