13185,IssuesEvent,2017-03-28 15:51:27+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,5345517,sebastian-luna-valero,6392739,conda,opened,Inconsistent dependency resolution,[],[],0,"
Hello,

If you do:
```
conda create --dry-run -n pysam pysam
```

you get `htslib-1.3.2-0` which is expected as requested in the `pysam` recipe:
https://github.com/bioconda/bioconda-recipes/blob/master/recipes/pysam/meta.yaml#L21

However, if you install `cgat-scripts-devel` which has `pysam` as dependency:
```
conda create --dry-run -n cgat cgat-scripts-devel 
```

you get `htslib-1.4-0` which contradicts the requirements of `pysam`.

Can you please explain why?

Here is the `.condarc`:
```
allow_softlinks: false

channels:
  - bioconda
  - r
  - defaults
  - conda-forge
```

