VUnit: 1.4.0

When generating codecs for a record with an array of a custom type, a compiler error is issued.
Should this be supported by the codec generator? Is there a work-around?

With a types in a types package defined as follows:
```
   type table_entry_t is record
      value : unsigned(4 downto 0);
      cell  : unsigned(10 downto 0);
   end record table_entry_t;

   type table_t is array (integer range <>) of table_entry_t;

   type cfg_t is record
      fixed_value : unsigned(7 downto 0);
      dly     : unsigned(7 downto 0);
      table   : table_t(31 downto 0);
   end record cfg_t;
```

I get an error when generating a codecs package (some info elided):
```
Compiling vunit_out\codecs\common\wfg_tb_msg_codecs_pkg.vhd into common ...
COMP96 ERROR COMP96_0124: ""Illegal prefix for attribute 'left."" ""<path>\wfg_tb_msg_codecs_pkg.vhd"" 509 89
