13566,IssuesEvent,2017-01-13 18:03:28+00:00,4127088,Azure/azure-sdk-for-python,1050156,lmazuel,6844498,Azure,closed,Implement Send Message batch for Service Bus,"[{'id': 117005107, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-sdk-for-python/labels/Feature', 'name': 'Feature', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}, {'id': 117005255, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-sdk-for-python/labels/Service%20Bus', 'name': 'Service Bus', 'color': '006b75', 'default': False}]",[],1,"Unlike Receive Message, there _is_ an API for [batch Send Message](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/azure/dn798894.aspx).

Please consider implementing this, or allowing a pull request for it. While using AMQP was recommended in [#459](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-python/issues/459) for high-performance because of HTTP limits, it's a massive pain to just install the AMQP Proton bindings because it needs to be built from the source. I actually save myself a lot of time by just switching to AWS Kinesis.

I don't need super high performance, it's just extremely inefficient to send hundreds of tiny 120-byte messages with the relatively huge HTTP header overhead.",{},{}
