      -DPYTHON_LIBRARY:FILEPATH=/Users/tantony/anaconda/lib/libpython3.5m.dylib ..
```

to try and build pybullet with Numpy support. I have numpy installed using Anaconda. However, I kept getting errors in the linking phase such as:
```Undefined symbols for architecture x86_64:
  ""_PyCObject_AsVoidPtr"", referenced from:
      _initpybullet in pybullet.c.o
  ""_PyCObject_Type"", referenced from:
