13714,IssuesEvent,2017-03-04 12:41:52+00:00,1605598,bulletphysics/bullet3,3111851,benelot,6955508,bulletphysics,closed,Concerning NaNs in pybullet,[],[],5,"I just had a RL agent trick me several times by sending NaN into my pybullet controlled simulation. I had this problem before with bullet physics that the rest of my simulator somehow produced NaNs and set them for positions or similar, which messed up the physics simulation. Given that people using pybullet may not be aware of such an issue, maybe it could help to check if values are numerical values (e.g. not NaN).",{},{}
