```

If I flip bob's admin credential on, all of a sudden this same query works.  Here's an authorization config for ""bob"" that works (all that changed is bobspartition/operator -> all-partitions/admin):

```
auth user bob {
    description bob
    encrypted-password $6$LsSnHp7J$AIJ2IC8kS.YDrrn/sH6BsxQgmm...
    partition Common
    partition-access {
        all-partitions {
            role admin
        }
    }
    shell tmsh
}
```

I talked to some folks who work on the control plane, and they say that if you want to use the REST API as a user who isn't the administrator, you must use token-based authentication.  Here's a description of how: https://devcentral.f5.com/wiki/icontrol.authentication_with_the_f5_rest_api.ashx . 

What I would like is a new option when constructing a BigIP object in f5-common-python that lets me ask for token-based auth.  Then I'd like the API to transparently get a token on my behalf (using username and password I provided) and store it in memory.  Whenever I make a request, it should use that token.

The tokens periodically expire, so we'd need some scheme to renew them.",{},{}
