14834,IssuesEvent,2016-03-03 17:20:22+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,295816,erikrose,9289019,letsencrypt,opened,Replace peep with pipstrap and pip 8,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/labels/letsencrypt-auto', 'name': 'letsencrypt-auto', 'color': '00a080'}]",[],0,"A [unicode error](https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/issues/2588#issuecomment-191472841) is biting a lot of people who have the several-year-old pip 1.5.4. It's likely a bug in that version of pip and, slightly less likely, in an old version of setuptools. Since pip 8 is now out, let's take replace peep with it (via embedding pipstrap), gain a more maintained installer, and dodge these bugs all in one fell swoop.",{},{}
