14923,IssuesEvent,2015-12-03 01:36:24+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,479213,pde,9289019,letsencrypt,closed,Webroot plugin should override permisions of files / dirs created,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/labels/webroot', 'name': 'webroot', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}]",[],6,"Running with --webroot-path and umask 0027 creates .well-known/acme-challenge/... with no global read permissions, causing the verification to fail because the HTTP server can't read the files (at least not in my setup).

Either overriding permissions during/after creation or making the directories and challenge file have similar permissions as the webroot itself should probably work in most cases.",{},{}
