15123,IssuesEvent,2017-12-05 14:39:56+00:00,9952134,python-visualization/folium,33519926,Conengmo,9969242,python-visualization,opened,Add support for arrays with NaNs or masked arrays,[],[],0,"One of my use cases for Folium is plotting GPS trajectories. I have this data in Numpy arrays, with a lot of NaNs when a part of the measurement didn't get through. Just removing the NaNs leads to invalid lines that can potentially cross large parts where no data was available. So I made some preprocessing to split the array in parts that are each valid, and plot the parts as PolyLines. 

I was wondering if this is functionality that is handy to include in Folium. Maybe a plugin that you can feed masked arrays or arrays with NaNs and that creates a group of PolyLines or a group of ColoredLines. Or maybe a general Line class in features that can handle anything? In conjunction with ColoredLines. Or keep the use case of Folium to 'perfect' data?

What do you guys think? ",{},{}
