15146,IssuesEvent,2017-09-05 12:40:33+00:00,9952134,python-visualization/folium,13682669,Brynnvincible,9969242,python-visualization,opened,Can't load file with GeoJson anymore,[],[],0,"If you try the following code on the current build you now get an error:

`folium.GeoJson(data=open(""somefile.json""))`

This results in the error:
`ValueError: Unhandled object <_io.TextIOWrapper...`

Looking at the __init__ function for GeoJson there is no code path that deals with this scenario anymore. But the comments for the class indicate that this is still supported, and the documentation example all use the class this way.

This can still be worked around by passing in a string or a dict, but it could break existing code for a lot of people if they update.",{},{}
15167,IssuesEvent,2017-04-03 03:39:07+00:00,42750248,watson-developer-cloud/python-sdk,26586734,labalekhan,10017763,watson-developer-cloud,opened,Using buffered files to create custom visual recognition classifier,[],[],0,"I am using IBM data Science Experience notebooks to create a custom classifier for the visual recognition service. I have the training zip files loaded into Object storage. But when I try to create the custom classifier it fails with the error message.

