15654,IssuesEvent,2017-10-12 20:49:41+00:00,41312700,symengine/symengine.py,7153935,cdiener,11509221,symengine,opened,Equality checks not consistent with sympy,[],[],0,"The following was a bit surprising to me:

```Python
In [96]: import symengine

In [97]: x, y = symengine.var(""x y"")

In [98]: x + y == x + y
Out[98]: True

In [99]: x + y + 0 == x + y
Out[99]: True

In [100]: x + y + 0.0 == x + y
Out[100]: False
```

In sympy `Out[100]` would be True.",{},{}
