ers/pnuu/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pnuu/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pnuu/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pnuu/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"Following something like that described here: https://opensource.google.com/docs/releasing/authors/

It would be nice to have an AUTHORS file to clean up the copyright statements in satpy to have some consistency. The basic idea is that all authors (names, usernames, and maybe email?) get added to the AUTHORS file and the copyright statement in each source code file would use ""Pytroll Developers"" on the copyright line.

Additionally, it would be nice to make the license/copyright statement more consistent. I would prefer that blank lines start with a `#` for consistency and to treat the whole block as one single block. I'll even go as far as saying I would like to remove the years from the copyright. My understanding is that the year in every source file is not needed and only needs to be updated in the main LICENSE file in the repository.

