16944,IssuesEvent,2017-05-31 16:06:31+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,16142208,jwhui,16142269,openthread,closed,nRF52840: Pass up link quality information of the ACK frames,"[{'id': 355043113, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openthread/openthread/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 397568864, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openthread/openthread/labels/P3', 'name': 'P3', 'color': 'DFDF00', 'default': False}, {'id': 549834395, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openthread/openthread/labels/platform:%20nrf52840', 'name': 'platform: nrf52840', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'hubertmis', 'id': 21953319, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/21953319?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hubertmis', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/hubertmis', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hubertmis/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hubertmis/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hubertmis/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hubertmis/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hubertmis/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hubertmis/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hubertmis/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hubertmis/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hubertmis/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"#1836 passed up the ACK Psdu, while the link quality information of the ACK frame is not passed up. Another enhancement in #1790 is that all ACK messages will be used for link quality evaluation, so it would be better to also pass up the link quality information of the ACK frames.",{},{}
16954,IssuesEvent,2017-12-03 00:19:07+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,16142208,jwhui,16142269,openthread,closed,[nrf52480] Calling nrf_drv_radio802154_fsm_sleep() breaks usb-cdc-uart transmit,"[{'id': 355043111, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openthread/openthread/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}, {'id': 397568693, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openthread/openthread/labels/P1', 'name': 'P1', 'color': 'DF3F00', 'default': False}, {'id': 549834395, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openthread/openthread/labels/platform:%20nrf52840', 'name': 'platform: nrf52840', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'rlubos', 'id': 22167799, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/22167799?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rlubos', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/rlubos', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rlubos/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rlubos/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rlubos/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rlubos/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rlubos/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rlubos/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rlubos/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rlubos/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/rlubos/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",5,"I am currently working on bringing up a nRF52480-based NCP that uses its native USB capabilities to communicate with the application/host processor, using [USB-CDC-ACM UART implementation](https://github.com/openthread/openthread/blob/master/examples/platforms/nrf52840/usb-cdc-uart.c) (Added in #2215, documented [here](https://github.com/openthread/openthread/tree/master/examples/platforms/nrf52840#native-usb-support)).

At first it seemed like it was working fairly well, but then I noticed that the NCP would become unresponsive after receiving certain commands. Depending on the command there were a few different reasons for this, but this bug is about the freeze that would happen after doing something like setting `PROP_NET_STACK_UP` to false.

When I would set `PROP_NET_STACK_UP` to false, I would no longer receive any output on the USB-CDC-ACM port. However, I know that the commands I was sending it were being received and processed.

Looking into the issue further made me realize that `ncp_uart.cpp` had called `otPlatUartSend()` to send the host the next frame, but `otPlatUartSendDone()` was not being called. Digging into this further, I determined that one of the results of setting `PROP_NET_STACK_UP` to false is a call to `otPlatRadioSleep()`. When I modified this function to return without doing anything, setting `PROP_NET_STACK_UP` to false would succeed.

Digging even further, I narrowed down the problem to the call to `nrf_drv_radio802154_fsm_sleep()` (Called from `nrf_drv_radio802154_request_sleep()`, which is called from `nrf_drv_radio802154_sleep()`, which is called from `otPlatRadioSleep()`). Calling `nrf_drv_radio802154_fsm_sleep()` somehow seems to quite reliably prevent future calls to `app_usbd_cdc_acm_write()` from triggering `APP_USBD_CDC_ACM_USER_EVT_TX_DONE`. It does not, however, prevent `APP_USBD_CDC_ACM_USER_EVT_RX_DONE` from being triggered, as even in this state the NCP continues to process inbound frames.
",{},{}
