17318,IssuesEvent,2017-03-17 03:46:12+00:00,51442999,python-cmd2/cmd2,2812720,tleonhardt,17161025,python-cmd2,closed,Add example of using regular expressions in a transcript test,"[{'id': 554473465, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/python-cmd2/cmd2/labels/documentation', 'name': 'documentation', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}, {'id': 324131052, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/python-cmd2/cmd2/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 324180750, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/python-cmd2/cmd2/labels/minor', 'name': 'minor', 'color': 'bfe5bf', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'tleonhardt', 'id': 2812720, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/2812720?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/tleonhardt', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/tleonhardt/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"The documentation states the following:

> Regular expressions can be embedded in the transcript inside paired / slashes. These regular expressions should not include any whitespace expressions.

But the example we have for using transcript testing doesn't include any regular expressions.

Add an example for how to this to make it easier for users to take advantage of this feature.

Also, we don't appear to have any unit tests which use a transcript with a regular expression embedded within it.  So we should add one.

If the feature doesn't work, we should either fix it or change the documentation.",{},{}
17354,IssuesEvent,2017-05-04 14:20:02+00:00,84221732,g8os/grid,6323012,serboctor,17511685,g8os,opened,Add validation for enums,"[{'id': 567320665, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/g8os/grid/labels/state_inprogress', 'name': 'state_inprogress', 'color': 'c2e0c6', 'default': False}, {'id': 555342643, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/g8os/grid/labels/type_bug', 'name': 'type_bug', 'color': 'fef2c0', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'serboctor', 'id': 6323012, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/6323012?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/serboctor', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/serboctor', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/serboctor/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/serboctor/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/serboctor/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/serboctor/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/serboctor/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/serboctor/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/serboctor/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/serboctor/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/serboctor/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"There is no validation done for any attribute that is expected to belong to a certain enum.
For example, in the bridge create, the networkMode is expected to be one of [""none"", ""static"", ""dnsmasq""]. If another value is supplied, the api doesn't validate and return a bad request which result in a crash in ays.

All payloads that contain enums should be validated and if a value other than the expected is supplied, the api should return a 400.
",{},{}
17381,IssuesEvent,2017-10-12 14:04:44+00:00,38581626,pybind/pybind11,8950602,trelau,17565521,pybind,opened,Compilation failure when binding type const char*,[],[],0,"## Issue description

Compilation failure when trying to compile the sample below (MSVC 2015 Windows 10 64-bit). This is a small replication of a C++ library that I am trying to wrap but cannot modify.

## Reproducible example code

```c++
#include <pybind11\pybind11.h>
#include <pybind11\iostream.h>

namespace py = pybind11;

typedef const char* TheString;

void TheMethod(TheString& theString) {
	std::cout << theString;
};



PYBIND11_MODULE(pymod2, mod) {

	mod.def(""TheMethod"", (void (*) (TheString&)) &TheMethod);
	
}
```
Results in:

`C2664	'void (TheString &)': cannot convert argument 1 from 'char *' to 'TheString &'`

Possibly related to https://github.com/pybind/pybind11/issues/1116",{},{}
17406,IssuesEvent,2018-06-16 18:32:33+00:00,38581626,pybind/pybind11,5349602,MisesEnForce,17565521,pybind,closed,Pyd module linking to the intel mkl,[],[],0,"The issue is linked with 

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/50878901/pybind11-vs-numpy-for-a-matrix-product

I have a perfectly fine pyd dll compiled with visual studio, providing a matrix product function. The c++ side of the algorithm is the standard way of computing a matrix product. Wanting to speed it up, I used the Intel MKL.

The loop

`for (int i = 0 ; i < nbRows1; ++i)
    {
        for (int j = 0 ; j < nbCols2; ++j)
        {
            for (int l = 0; l < nbCols1; ++l)
            {
                localSum += ptr1[nbCols1 * i + l] * ptr2[nbCols2 * l + j];
            }
            ptr[nbCols2 * i + j] = localSum;
            localSum = 0.0;
        }
    }`

is therefor simply replaced with : 

`cblas_dgemm(CblasRowMajor, CblasNoTrans, CblasNoTrans, nbRows1, nbCols2, nbCols1, 1.0, ptr1, nbRows1, ptr2, nbCols2, 0.0, ptr, nbRows1);`

In the visual studio project build the pyd, I added the mkl include directory to the additional include directory, and did the analogue for the additional library directories.

When I run the python, I get a cryptic ""ImportError: DLL load failed: The specified module could not be found"" trigger by the line where I import my module.",{},{}
