17719,IssuesEvent,2018-07-05 14:50:03+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,310139,hackaugusto,19666847,raiden-network,closed,Refactor secret unlock logic,"[{'id': 974626734, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw5NzQ2MjY3MzQ=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/P1', 'name': 'P1', 'color': '683faf', 'default': False}, {'id': 953951221, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw5NTM5NTEyMjE=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/meta', 'name': 'meta', 'color': '1d76db', 'default': False}]",[],3,"Secret unlock logic has been changed.  Instead of needing to `unlock` each secret, we now have a batch unlock after the channel has been settled.

TODO:

- [x] add the `SecretRegistry` proxy instance to be available inside the `RaidenService` - https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/issues/1587
- [x] Take SecretRegistry into account in the state machine - https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/issues/1579
- [x] Add on-chain secret reveal if a secret is about to expire - https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/issues/1584
- [x] Remove logic for closing the channel if a secret is about to expire - https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/issues/1617
- [ ] `transfer/mediated_transfer/target.py` - `handle_inittarget` - rethink `safe_to_wait` in this context, as we only have 1 on-chain transaction now. - https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/issues/1603

2. Add batch unlock state changes and events
- [x] move unlock from `handle_channel_closed` to `handle_channel_settled` in `transfer.channel.py`
- [x] `get_known_unlocks` used now in `handle_channel_settled` should return the packed pending transfers data instead of an array of locks.
- [x] `handle_contract_channelunlock` which handles sending the `unlock` transaction to the contract, now needs to send 1 transaction with the packed data instead of multiple transactions for each lock
- [x] `ContractReceiveChannelUnlock` state change with new data returned by the `ChannelUnlocked`
- [x] handle `ChannelUnlocked` event; it is currently handled by `handle_channel_withdraw` (`blockchain_events_handler.py`). This is a bad name for this functionality. Consider `handle_channel_unlock`. - fixed in https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/pull/1540
- [ ] limit the number of pending transfers to the gas limit needed to unlock them all - https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/issues/439  <--- Required only for the mainnet red eyes release

This issue needs more details regarding messages and protocol changes. May need further splitting into issues.

Note:
- for batch unlocking, we can choose between having it as a user-triggered action and doing it automatically after the channel is settled. We are going with the latter, because the first option also needs additional work for adding proper REST APIs & web UI changes.
",{},{}
17720,IssuesEvent,2017-02-06 14:08:33+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,7483198,nicksavers,19666847,raiden-network,closed,The 'ethereum' distribution was not found and is required by raiden,[],[],1,"## Problem Definition

During the build `python setup.py develop` running in a clean `virtualenv` as described in the [PoC-0](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/wiki/Raiden-PoC%E2%80%900#install) installation manual, the following error occurs:

```
