18246,IssuesEvent,2018-08-06 07:02:33+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,1396878,gravyboat,22243823,streamlink,closed,"Twitch has removed the ""/api/v2/clips/"" endpoint - VODs broken","[{'id': 613834511, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw2MTM4MzQ1MTE=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/streamlink/streamlink/labels/plugin%20issue', 'name': 'plugin issue', 'color': 'ff6633', 'default': False}]",[],4,"## Plugin Issue

- [X] This is a plugin issue and I have read the contribution guidelines.

### Description

When given a video (VOD) URL like https://www.twitch.tv/entropicj/video/12345678, the Twitch plugin checks the status and sources of that video by calling

    return http.json(self.call_subdomain(""clips"", ""/api/v2/clips/"" + clip_name + ""/status"", format="""")

Unfortunately this API endpoint recently got removed, so that watching VODs is currently impossible.

