18315,IssuesEvent,2018-07-18 08:07:21+00:00,94917848,jupyterlab/jupyterlab-git,510760,vidartf,22800682,jupyterlab,opened,Add extension point: Diff viewers,[],[],0,"I'm working on [nbdime](https://github.com/jupyter/nbdime), which also has a jupyterlab extension. Currently the labextension only supports diffing the current version of the file on disk vs git HEAD. While this is useful, if it was integrated with jupyterlab-git, it could support diffing any git refs of notebooks. This would help push use of git/VCS for notebooks, which is a Good Thing!

There are many ways to achieve such an integration, but I think my favorite is like this:
- the jupyterlab-git extension provides an interface, with a function for registering a diff provider, e.g. with a signature like this: `registerDiffProvider(fileExtensions: string[], provider: (path: string, revA: string, revB: string) => void): void` (or possibly, define an interface for the diff provider). It could then also have a helper function to get the notebook content for a specific revision (`getFile(path: string, revision: string): INotebook`).
- jupyterlab-git might then want to supply a default diff viewer (line-based string differ) based on a standard JS diff lib.

The advantages to this approach:
- no dependencies for jupyterlab-git.
- providers like nbdime can have an optional requires of the provided interface!
- easy for third-party developers to add support for more file formats (e.g. Word or PDF files).
- simple API.",{},{}
