Small work example:

```
import ipywidgets as ipw
from IPython.display import display

st = {'description_width': '250px'}
lt = ipw.Layout(width = '600px')

D = ipw.Dropdown(
    options = ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e'],
    value = 'a',
    description = ""Some parameter a:"",
    disabled = False,
    style = st,
    layout = lt
)

TB = ipw.IntText(
    value = 5,
    min = 1,
    max = 10,
    description = ""Other parameter b:"",
    disabled = False,
    style = st,
    layout = lt
)

#TB.layout.display = 'none'
display(D, TB)
```

When `TB.layout.display = 'none'` is commented, all widgets are visible. When I uncomment this line, I don't see any widgets. I use chrome devtools and see that all widgets begin `display='none'`, although I wanted to make only one widget hidden.

Is this a bug? If no, what I do wrong? Please, help.

Best regards,
Andrey.",{},{}
