18543,IssuesEvent,2018-03-08 22:12:23+00:00,71482397,Parsl/parsl,5114833,annawoodard,26490185,Parsl,opened,Tweak documentation organization,[],[],0,"The documentation is already in awesome shape-- this is just a minor thing that occurs to me while reading through it. We currently have class documentation under `Developer documentation` -> `Developer documentation`. I think we should reorganize that a bit to remove the redundancy. We currently have a very nice layout:

1. Quickstart
2. User guide (includes overview, detailed descriptions of various components, FAQ)
3. Developer documentation

As a new user, you'd probably see 'Developer documentation' and assume that was for Parsl devs only. But class documentation for user-facing classes is clearly relevant for them too. Sometimes, especially users that are relatively familiar with Parsl, but want to quickly figure out what the options are for a particular class want to quickly look up the class documentation and not have to search through the detailed descriptions. I vote to add a fourth section, after the User guide, called `Class documentation` or similar, which only contains the class documentation.",{},{}
