18572,IssuesEvent,2018-06-11 16:57:13+00:00,87358890,KrishnaswamyLab/PHATE,22503949,kmoon3,26941417,KrishnaswamyLab,closed,PHATE for single cell HiC data?,[],"[{'login': 'kmoon3', 'id': 22503949, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjIyNTAzOTQ5', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/22503949?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kmoon3', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/kmoon3', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kmoon3/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kmoon3/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kmoon3/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kmoon3/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kmoon3/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kmoon3/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kmoon3/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kmoon3/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kmoon3/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"Hello,
Compared to population based HiC data, single cell HiC data are very sparse and hence good imputation methods are needed to fill in the contact matrix. 
In line with that, can I use PHATE directly on a very sparse single cell contact matrix? Or will I need to use MAGIC for imputation and then use PHATE on the imputed contact matrix?
Any suggestions will be great!

Also in the age of single cell HiC, it would be awesome if there were some examples of the same in PHATE and/or MAGIC tutorials.
 
Thanks.",{},{}
