18718,IssuesEvent,2018-02-16 23:58:03+00:00,102692863,onnx/onnx,17890620,dzhulgakov,31675368,onnx,opened,Simple optimization pass: fuse Conv+Add into Conv with Bias,"[{'id': 685678340, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/onnx/onnx/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 685678342, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/onnx/onnx/labels/good%20first%20issue', 'name': 'good first issue', 'color': '7057ff', 'default': True}, {'id': 685678341, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/onnx/onnx/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '33aa3f', 'default': True}, {'id': 815747198, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/onnx/onnx/labels/optimizer', 'name': 'optimizer', 'color': '63a5cc', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Conv in onnx spec supports embedded bias as it's often represented this way in accelerated backends: https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/master/docs/Operators.md#conv

However, some exporters produce separate Conv and Add operators. We should fuse them if bias is 1-d in this case and have it available as optimization pass (https://github.com/onnx/onnx/tree/master/onnx/optimizer/passes)",{},{}
